NAME
    sed - stream editor for filtering and transforming text

SYNOPSIS
    sed [OPTION]... SCRIPT [FILE]...
    sed [OPTION]... -e SCRIPT... [FILE]...
    sed [OPTION]... -f SCRIPT-FILE [FILE]...

DESCRIPTION
    sed is a stream editor that reads input line by line, applies editing
    commands, and writes the result to standard output. With no FILE or
    when FILE is '-', read standard input.

OPTIONS
    -e SCRIPT, --expression=SCRIPT
        Add the commands in SCRIPT to the set of commands to execute.
        Multiple -e options may be given.

    -f FILE, --file=FILE
        Add the commands contained in FILE to the set of commands.

    -i[SUFFIX], --in-place[=SUFFIX]
        Edit files in-place. If SUFFIX is provided, a backup is made
        with that suffix before editing.

    -n, --quiet, --silent
        Suppress automatic printing of pattern space.

    -E, -r, --regexp-extended
        Use extended regular expressions (ERE) in the script.

    --version
        Output version information and exit.

    --help
        Display help and exit.

COMMANDS
    d       Delete pattern space; start next cycle.

    p       Print pattern space.

    q [N]   Quit with optional exit code N.

    s/RE/REPLACEMENT/[FLAGS]
        Substitute RE with REPLACEMENT. FLAGS: g (global), i (ignore
        case), N (substitute Nth occurrence), p (print if substituted).

    y/SRC/DST/
        Transliterate characters in SRC to corresponding chars in DST.

    a TEXT  Append TEXT after the current line.

    i TEXT  Insert TEXT before the current line.

    c TEXT  Replace the current line with TEXT.

    n       Print pattern space, read next line into pattern space.

    N       Append next line to pattern space with embedded newline.

    =       Print the current input line number.

    r FILE  Append contents of FILE to output.

    { ... } Group commands.

    ADDR    Commands may be prefixed with a line number, a regex
            /PATTERN/, or a range ADDR1,ADDR2.

EXAMPLES
    sed 's/foo/bar/' file.txt
        Replace first 'foo' with 'bar' on each line.

    sed 's/foo/bar/g' file.txt
        Replace all occurrences of 'foo' with 'bar'.

    sed -n '/error/p' log.txt
        Print only lines matching 'error'.

    sed '5,10d' file.txt
        Delete lines 5 through 10.

    sed -i.bak 's/old/new/g' config.txt
        Edit config.txt in-place, backup to config.txt.bak.

    sed '/^#/d' config.conf
        Remove comment lines.

EXIT STATUS
    0   Success.
    1   Error in usage or in a script.
